claim.claim-text:
A method (702) of manufacturing a flanged composite component (12), the method comprising:
coupling a composite structure to (90) a first composite material (86);
coupling a second composite material (88) to the composite structure;
placing a first expansion device (28) within the second composite material (88);
coupling a forming element (24) to at least one of the first composite material, the composite structure, and the second composite material against a mold (22);
coupling a pressure element (26) to the forming element (24) to define a space (68) among the mold, the forming element and the pressure element; and
expanding the first expansion device (28) to impart a force to the second composite material to (88) move the second composite material away from the composite structure (90) and into the space (68) to facilitate forming a first flange (18).

An apparatus for manufacturing a flanged composite component (12), said apparatus comprising:
a mold (22) configured to couple to a composite material (88);
a forming element (24) coupled to said mold;
a pressure element (26) coupled to said forming element to define a space (68) among said mold, said forming element and said pressure element;
an expansion device (28) is disposed within said composite material (88), said expansion device is configured to impart a forming force to said forming element and said pressure element; and
a positioner (32) is disposed within said composite material (88) and in contact with said expansion device (28) and configured to facilitate positioning said expansion device within said space.
